<FIRST>r a PM-CourtShooting 1stLd-Writethru a0442 04-08 0372</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Court Shooting, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0442,0378</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gunman Kills Judge, Wounds Police Officer</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with hometown of gunman, condition of wounded
officer, quote from police chief's wife. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALACIOS, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A masked gunman killed a judge in a
courthouse annex and critically wounded a police officer before he
was fatally wounded in a shootout, authorities said.
   Police said they have no motive in Friday's shootings.
   Killed was Justice of the Peace Jack Dooley, 79. Assistant
Police Chief Emmitt Greene was shot in the chest, said Police Chief
Don Gullett. Greene was in serious condition Friday night at
Matagorda General Hospital in Bay City.
   The gunman was identified as Duc Nga Nguyen, 27, from Garden
City, Kan.
   Nguyen had been at the annex earlier in the day inquiring about
obtaining a driver's license and left when he was told they were
only issued on Wednesday.
   Nguyen returned later wearing a cap and a bandanna over his
face, said Gullett. Nguyen also wore a backpack that, police later
learned, contained adhesive tape, string and a device that could be
used as a bomb detonator. The pack also contained three pairs of
fake handcuffs.
   Pam Gullett, the police chief's wife who works for the county
tax office, said she knew there was something wrong as soon as
Nguyen walked in.
   ``He yelled at me to stand up. I asked him what he said, and
then the shooting started,'' she said. ``I ducked into a corner,
hoping that the bullets wouldn't go through the wood.''
   Dooley walked in as Nguyen grabbed a 32-year-old man, who was
standing by the door, authorities said.
   ``Judge Jack Dooley came upon them, he (Nguyen) looked at him,
pointed a gun and shot him once in the heart,'' said Matagorda
County Sheriff Sam Hurta.
   After the shot was fired, Greene ordered Nguyen to drop the gun,
but Nguyen began firing. Greene was hit in the chest, but was able
to reload his .45-caliber revolver and kill the gunman.
   ``About 18 to 20 rounds were exchanged,'' Gullett said.
   Police said Nguyen had been arrested in Palacios in 1987 for
carrying a pistol. Palacios is on the Texas Gulf Coast about 100
miles southwest of Houston.
</TEXT>
