<HEAD>Violent Clashes Accompany Ultra-Rightist Rally</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASCHAFFENBURG, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Protesters hurled rocks and
bottles and attacked police with nails outside a village meeting
hall where members of the ultra-right Republicans Party held a
rally, officials said Saturday.
   Police said 17 people were injured and seven protesters were
arrested in the clashes Friday night in Grossostheim, a village
outside Aschaffenburg, about 25 miles southeast of Frankfurt.
   Officials said protesters smashed store windows and damaged
police vehicles.
   The violence erupted after about 500 demonstrators broke off
from a peaceful protest attended by about 1,400 people and marched
toward the building where the Republicans' rally drew 1,300, police
said.
