<HEAD>Bus Crashes in Algarve Killing 13 Soccer Fans, 28 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTIMAO, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus carrying socccer fans crashed
early Saturday in the southern Algarve region, killing 13 people
and injuring at least 28, police said.
   A spokesman for the National Republican Guard said the bus
swerved off the road near the town of Bartolomeu de Messines and
landed upside down, trapping some passengers inside.
   The town is about 180 miles south of Lisbon.
   A tire blow-out was the likely cause of the accident, the
spokesman said on condition of anonymity.
   The Portuguese news agency Lusa reported two cranes had to right
the bus before the dead and injured could be removed and
transported to hospitals.
   The bus was carrying supporters of an Algarve soccer team to a
match in northern Oporto, the agency reported.
   The bus was licensed to carry 46 people, but it was not sure how
many passengers were on board, Lusa said.
